op enablement\n    38\t- [x] support interval presets such as `10 min` and `20 min`\n    39\t- [x] support a custom interval input\n    40\t- [x] show whether a card is currently loop-managed\n    41\t\n    42\t### Task 4 — Runtime Control Actions\n    43\t\n    44\t- [x] start loop from the extension\n    45\t- [x] stop loop from the extension\n    46\t- [x] restart loop from the extension\n    47\t- [x] keep the UI state consistent when the daemon exits unexpectedly\n    48\t\n    17\t## Current Slice\n    18\t\n    19\t- [ ] Track exit review — confirm `task-plans/codex-loop-control-surface-task-plan.md` can close before moving to the next follow-on track.\n    20\t\n    21\t## Next Handoff\n    22\t\n    23\t- Keep the next step scoped to a track exit review for `task-plans/codex-loop-control-surface-task-plan.md`; do not open the next follow-on track until this closure is explicit.\n    24\t- The communication-optimization track is complete.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
